cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MS

The paper proposes a novel generative model that combines convolutional neural networks and generative adversarial networks to generate virtual patients for pre-procedural planning in complex surgeries. This involves feature selection and mapping that is pathophysiologically interpretable. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel generative model that uses machine learning techniques to generate virtual patients for pre-procedural planning in complex surgeries.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper uses convolutional neural networks to extract features from medical images and generate virtual patients that are visually authentic.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel AI-based approach to generate virtual patients for pre-procedural planning in complex surgeries.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses generative adversarial networks to generate virtual patients that are visually authentic and pathophysiologically interpretable.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper may involve the development of mathematical software for implementing the proposed generative model.
